      <h2>Construction &amp; Renovation in Kahului</h2>
      <p>Kahului is the commercial and logistical center of Maui. It's where goods arrive at the port, where passengers touch down at Kahului Airport, where the big-box stores, shopping centers, and light industrial operations that support the entire island are concentrated. The Queen Ka'ahumanu Center, the Maui Mall, Costco, Home Depot, and the industrial corridor along Hana Highway and the harbor area make Kahului the commercial engine of Maui's economy.</p>

      <p>As Maui's commercial center, Kahului is also one of the island's most active renovation and construction markets. Businesses open, expand, and reconfigure their spaces at a higher rate than anywhere else on Maui. Commercial tenant improvements — office buildouts, retail renovations, restaurant renovations, and warehouse modifications — are a constant in Kahului's commercial real estate market.</p>

      <p>Great General LLC is active in Kahului's commercial renovation market. We provide general contracting services for commercial tenant improvements, interior buildouts, and renovations for businesses throughout the Kahului commercial district, the industrial area near the harbor, and the surrounding commercial nodes along the main corridors.</p>

      <h2>Commercial Tenant Improvements in Kahului</h2>
      <p>A commercial tenant improvement (TI) is a renovation or buildout of a commercial space — an office suite, retail unit, restaurant, or warehouse — to fit the specific needs of a tenant. In Kahului, where commercial real estate turns over regularly and businesses expand into new spaces, tenant improvements are common and often involve tight timelines tied to lease commencement dates.</p>

      <p>We handle commercial TI projects in Kahului including:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Office buildouts and renovations</strong> — partition walls, conference rooms, break rooms, reception areas, and the framing, drywall, flooring, and finish work that transforms raw office space into a functional workspace. We handle Maui County commercial permits and coordinate with electrical and plumbing contractors.</li>
        <li><strong>Retail renovations</strong> — storefront improvements, interior layout modifications, display fixture installations, and the finish work that creates a compelling retail environment. We understand the timeline pressure of retail openings and manage projects accordingly.</li>
        <li><strong>Restaurant renovations</strong> — kitchen buildouts, dining room renovations, bar construction, and the specialized framing and finish work that restaurant spaces require. We coordinate with plumbing, electrical, and mechanical contractors who hold the licenses for those trades.</li>
        <li><strong>Warehouse modifications</strong> — interior wall additions, office infills within warehouse spaces, loading dock improvements, and the structural and finish work that makes warehouse and light industrial spaces functional for their intended use.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Kahului's Industrial and Light Commercial Zone</h2>
      <p>The industrial area around Kahului Harbor and extending along Amala Place, Hobron Avenue, and the surrounding streets hosts Maui's warehousing, marine, auto, and light manufacturing businesses. We work in this zone on warehouse interior modifications, office infill buildouts within industrial buildings, and the structural and finish work that businesses in this area need as they expand and evolve.</p>

      <p>The harbor area specifically presents construction challenges related to its coastal location. Salt-air exposure affects exterior and semi-exposed metalwork significantly in this zone. We spec corrosion-resistant materials for any metalwork in or near the harbor area — a consideration that matters more than most clients initially realize.</p>

      <h2>Residential Renovation in Kahului</h2>
      <p>While Kahului is primarily known as a commercial center, it has substantial residential neighborhoods — older neighborhoods near the airport and commercial district, and the more recent residential development extending toward the Kahului Airport Road corridor and beyond. Many of these homes are occupied by Maui families who've lived here for generations, and renovation work in these neighborhoods involves a mix of modernization and respectful maintenance of character.</p>

      <p>We do kitchen remodels, bathroom renovations, interior framing, drywall, flooring, and general contracting for Kahului homeowners. We're familiar with the older housing stock in this part of Maui and the renovation considerations that come with it.</p>

      <h2>Proximity to the Airport — Project Logistics</h2>
      <p>One often-overlooked advantage of Kahului-area projects is the proximity to the airport and Kahului's supply chain infrastructure. Material deliveries from the mainland arrive most efficiently at the Kahului port and airport, which is a practical consideration for large renovation projects that require significant material procurement. Working in Kahului, we're at the center of that supply chain rather than managing deliveries to remote parts of the island.</p>

      <h2>Services Available in Kahului</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Commercial tenant improvements — office, retail, restaurant, and warehouse buildouts</li>
        <li>Residential renovation — kitchen and bathroom remodels, interior framing, drywall, flooring, and carpentry</li>
        <li>General contracting and project management including Maui County commercial permits</li>
        <li>Interior demolition — selective and full gut</li>
        <li>Custom carpentry and millwork for commercial and residential applications</li>
        <li>Metal fabrication — custom gates, railings, security screens, and commercial metalwork</li>
        <li>Coordination with licensed specialty trades — electrical, plumbing, HVAC</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Maui County Permitting for Commercial Projects</h2>
      <p>Commercial construction and tenant improvement projects in Kahului require Maui County Department of Public Works permits for any work that affects the structure, plumbing, electrical, or mechanical systems — which is most meaningful TI work. We manage the commercial permit process including plan preparation, submittal, review coordination, and inspection scheduling. This is included in our general contracting scope, not an add-on.</p>

      <h2>Free On-Site Estimates in Kahului</h2>
      <p>If you have a commercial or residential construction project in Kahului or the broader Central Maui area, we'll come to your site for a free estimate. Call (808) 795-4044 or request an estimate online.</p>
